	 <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520"> 
		<head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head> 
		<p>Correspondence and records of the Alumni Office and its regional
		  clubs; include records of Cornell Day celebration also correspondence
		  (1911-1918) concerning the Advisor of Women's position originally held by
		  Mrs.Gertrude S. Martin, including letters from Mrs. Martin and women in various
		  Cornell Clubs to President Schurman expressing their concern that the position
		  was not a faculty one.</p> 
		<p>Also 5 films from Southwest Regional Office. Various Cornell buttons
		  from the Northeast Regional Office.</p> 
		<p>Also 12 Cornell buttons.</p> 
	 </scopecontent> 
